Training Neural Network¶

Inputs: KM, Manufactue Date </br> Output: Rate (%) in the range [0,1]

In [47]:
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(32, input_shape=(2,), activation='tanh'))
# model.add(Dense(16, activation='tanh'))
model.add(Dense(16, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(4, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
# Compile model
model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
In [48]:
history = model.fit(X, y, epochs=10000, batch_size = 64, validation_split=0.1)

Model 1 Epochs Vs. Loss Plot¶

At MSE = 0.05 the model seems to have similar training and validation loss value.</br> After that over fitting caused validation loss to increase significantly.

One Solution: More training data

Model 2 Epochs Vs. Loss Plot¶

At MSE = 0.045 the model seems to have similar training and validation loss value.</br> After that over fitting caused validation loss to increase significantly.

One Solution: More training data

In [52]:
history_df = pd.DataFrame(history.history)
plt.title('model loss')
plt.ylabel('MSE')
plt.xlabel('epoch')
plt.plot(history_df['loss'], label='loss')
plt.plot(history_df['val_loss'], label='val_loss')

plt.legend()
